  this manifest deletes them from the org. As of 2026-06-09 a check-only delete
  against staging fails for all six with:
      "insufficient access rights on cross-reference id"
  i.e. the deploying user (webdev5) lacks rights to delete them, or an
  out-of-source component still references them. Resolve that (run as an admin
  with Manage Flow + Modify All Data, deactivate any lingering versions, or
  clear the cross-reference), then deploy:

      sf project deploy start \
        --manifest manifest/flow-cleanup/package.xml \
        --post-destructive-changes manifest/flow-cleanup/destructiveChangesPost.xml \
        --target-org "$SF_TARGET_ORG"

  Apply to production at the Phase 6 cutover as well.
-->
